# BUG-638 — response-shape Zod validation guard allowlist.
#
# Each non-empty / non-comment line is a `<file>:<lineNo>` signature
# permitting a non-canonical `res.json()` call. Use sparingly — every entry is
# a documented exception to CLAUDE.md §5.2 ("Backend must map snake_case DB
# columns to camelCase response fields. Never pass raw Knex rows directly to
# res.json()").
#
# Format: `<relative-file-path>:<lineNo>  # cascade-BUG-id — reason`
#
# All grandfathered entries cite BUG-638-CASCADE-MIGRATE-MAPPER-CONSUMERS,
# the umbrella cascade that tracks migration of pre-existing routes to the
# canonical mapper pattern (sibling of BUG-613/618/622). Entries are
# prioritised by clinical-safety surface in the cascade BUG.
#
# Prefer the inline `// @response-shape-exempt: <reason>` annotation on the
# line directly above the res.json() call — keeps the exception co-located
# with the code that needs it. Use this allowlist file when the inline
# annotation is impractical (high churn).
#
# This file is auto-populated by the initial guard run; subsequent
# allowlist entries should be reviewed manually.
# Expiry-policy: per-entry (added 2026-05-03 cycle Phase 0a.7)
# Each non-comment line carries an `| expires: <YYYY-MM-DD> (cascade: <BUG>)`
# OR `| permanent: <reason>` annotation. Entries past their expiry date
# fail the merge gate via `scripts/guards/check-allowlist-expiry.ts`.
# Renewal: when a target close-by date passes, EITHER drain the entry
# (preferred) OR explicitly extend the date with operator authorization.
